WEBVTT

00:02.036 --> 00:03.471
Previously on "Chance"...

00:03.504 --> 00:04.672
Doctor Chance? Detective Hynes,
Fremont P.D.

00:04.705 --> 00:06.240
How'd you know
to talk to Cohen, again?

00:06.274 --> 00:07.475
We were colleagues.

00:07.508 --> 00:09.343
You sleep with her?
No.

00:09.377 --> 00:11.079
Just surprising
that somebody was

00:11.112 --> 00:12.646
inquiring about
Myra is all.

00:12.680 --> 00:15.716
You never know where a lead
could come from, or when.

00:15.749 --> 00:17.351
Hey, Frank!

00:17.385 --> 00:19.087
Put your hands
on the bumper there.

00:19.120 --> 00:21.989
[ Grunting ]

00:22.022 --> 00:23.324
Stay away from my wife!

00:23.357 --> 00:24.725
And that's the last piece
of friendly advice

00:24.758 --> 00:25.993
you're ever gonna get.

00:26.026 --> 00:27.161
Just tell me what happened!

00:27.195 --> 00:28.662
Blackstone
pops right out the door

00:28.696 --> 00:29.997
like the guy
had signaled him.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.499
That's when I put one
in his chest.

00:31.532 --> 00:32.666
So, you killed him?

00:32.700 --> 00:34.368
Well, he took
a kill shot, for sure.

00:34.402 --> 00:36.437
I brought you this drive,
if you still want it.

00:36.470 --> 00:39.107
It's all just police reports,
his cases, I guess.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.375
So, a guy died tonight
for basically nothing.

00:41.409 --> 00:43.444
I would have killed
my father if I could've.

00:43.477 --> 00:45.113
I would have
scalped the fucker.

00:45.146 --> 00:47.548
[ Indistinct talking ]

00:49.783 --> 00:51.285
Shh!

00:51.319 --> 00:53.387
[ Indistinct talking continues ]

00:56.624 --> 00:58.392
[ Thud ]

01:04.064 --> 01:07.668
**

01:54.382 --> 01:55.749
Woman: Is he breathing?

01:55.783 --> 01:59.086
He's diaphoretic,
he's tachycardic, thready pulse.

01:59.119 --> 02:00.454
Breath rate of about
six per minute.

02:00.488 --> 02:02.089
No sign of trauma,

02:02.122 --> 02:04.625
and I can't be sure about
a heart attack or stroke.

02:04.658 --> 02:07.295
Hold on one second, sir.

02:09.297 --> 02:11.699
-Darius Pringle.
-Are you still there?

02:11.732 --> 02:13.301
Fuck!

02:13.334 --> 02:14.635
Sorry.

02:14.668 --> 02:17.104
Patient's medicating
for Type 2 diabetes

02:17.137 --> 02:18.272
and sleep apnea.

02:18.306 --> 02:20.107
-Are you a physician?
-Yes.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.776
We have an ambulance
en route to 6600 Post Street.

02:22.810 --> 02:24.812
Are you the patient's doctor?
-No.

02:24.845 --> 02:27.481
Just his friend.

02:37.591 --> 02:41.562
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. system ]

02:43.731 --> 02:45.299
Christina: Hi.
You've reached Christina.

02:45.333 --> 02:46.634
Leave a message
at the beep.

02:46.667 --> 02:47.701
Thanks.

02:47.735 --> 02:49.136
[ Beep ]

02:49.169 --> 02:50.638
Hi, Christina, it's me.

02:50.671 --> 02:53.574
I have to talk to you,
right now. I mean it.

02:53.607 --> 02:55.243
I don't care where you are
or what you're doing,

02:55.276 --> 02:56.510
you call me as soon
as you get this.

02:56.544 --> 02:59.179
All right?
Call me.

03:02.583 --> 03:04.151
My God.
What's it been?

03:04.184 --> 03:06.654
Only forever.

03:06.687 --> 03:08.522
Ginley.

03:08.556 --> 03:09.723
My God.
You're still here.

03:09.757 --> 03:11.659
Where else am I gonna be?

03:11.692 --> 03:12.693
You look terrible.

03:12.726 --> 03:14.262
Thanks.

03:14.295 --> 03:15.696
How's your patient?

03:15.729 --> 03:17.731
Uh, no.
He's not my patient.

03:17.765 --> 03:19.333
He's --
He's just a friend.

03:19.367 --> 03:21.769
I was visiting
and found him like this.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.437
I'm sorry, Eldon.

03:23.471 --> 03:25.339
Just assumed
he was yours.

03:25.373 --> 03:27.775
Pulled his file,
if you're interested.

03:27.808 --> 03:30.511
Uh, yes.
Yes, I am.

03:30.544 --> 03:33.614
I mean, he's not my patient now,
but I intend that he will be.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.353
E.R. doctor
was asking for everything

03:39.387 --> 03:41.855
we could find, and Mr. Pringle
here was in our database,

03:41.889 --> 03:46.193
along with records from
Fort Miley and Napa State.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.195
Well, he's a vet.

03:48.228 --> 03:52.199
I get Fort Miley,
but Napa State?

03:52.232 --> 03:54.568
The story's in the history
on this one.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.406
Can I, maybe,
get a look at that?

04:01.609 --> 04:02.876
I'll print you out a copy.

04:02.910 --> 04:06.547
You just didn't
get it from me.

04:06.580 --> 04:07.915
Of course.
That's a young man

04:07.948 --> 04:11.752
who could use
someone good on his side.

04:11.785 --> 04:14.422
Thanks, Ginley.

04:25.699 --> 04:29.903
Darius Pringle is a 36-year-old
right-handed white male,

04:29.937 --> 04:31.572
born the younger
of two children,

04:31.605 --> 04:34.241
having a brother
three years his senior.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.910
His father is a PhD
theoretical physicist.

04:36.944 --> 04:39.246
His mother was
a classical violinist

04:39.279 --> 04:40.914
who toured
and recorded extensively

04:40.948 --> 04:42.516
in Europe
and the United States.

04:42.550 --> 04:44.585
At the age of 9, Darius,

04:44.618 --> 04:46.820
along with his mother
and 12-year-old brother

04:46.854 --> 04:48.689
were struck
by a drunk driver

04:48.722 --> 04:51.659
while on a crosswalk
in residential San Francisco.

04:51.692 --> 04:54.294
No!
His mother and brother
died instantly.

04:56.397 --> 04:57.631
Darius spent four weeks

04:57.665 --> 05:00.468
at San Francisco
General Hospital.

05:00.501 --> 05:04.505
CT scans reported a right
frontal subdural hematoma.

05:04.538 --> 05:08.542
[ Cellphone rings ]

05:08.576 --> 05:09.777
-Yeah?
-I was in the shower.

05:09.810 --> 05:11.445
I -- I didn't sleep all night.

05:11.479 --> 05:12.946
I just laid there
thinking about Nicky.

05:12.980 --> 05:15.649
-Is Neil there?
-I told you, the biking trip,

05:15.683 --> 05:17.451
three nights
camping at Half Moon Bay.

05:17.485 --> 05:18.652
Okay. Lock the doors.

05:18.686 --> 05:20.287
I'll be right there.
-What?

05:20.320 --> 05:22.322
I'll call you from
outside the house.

05:26.394 --> 05:27.795
-You're scaring me.
-I don't know how else

05:27.828 --> 05:29.363
to make you
take this seriously.

05:29.397 --> 05:30.898
Okay, so then, maybe
I should go wake up Nicky.

05:30.931 --> 05:32.966
You can wake her up in a minute.
Just listen to me now, okay?

05:33.000 --> 05:34.702
You have to pack enough
to last you both a while,

05:34.735 --> 05:36.303
then just get on the road.

05:36.336 --> 05:38.038
Don't tell people
where you're going, all right?

05:38.071 --> 05:39.640
Not even Neil.
You go somewhere,

05:39.673 --> 05:41.341
you stay there
until you hear from me.

05:41.375 --> 05:43.310
You can't come in here
and just tell me to do this

05:43.343 --> 05:44.645
and not let me ask
any questions.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.480
Is this something
to do with a patient?

05:46.514 --> 05:48.516
Is it someone that's fixating?
Is it someone that's violent?

05:48.549 --> 05:50.317
It's connected to
a patient, yes.

05:50.350 --> 05:51.819
Then let's go talk
to the police.

05:51.852 --> 05:53.587
We can't go to the police!
The police won't do anything.

05:53.621 --> 05:54.722
We have to
protect ourselves.

05:54.755 --> 05:56.356
Okay?
Please, Christina.

05:56.390 --> 05:57.658
Please, just trust me.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.993
I -- I don't --
Where do I go?

06:00.027 --> 06:02.830
My mother's?
What about Liz?

06:02.863 --> 06:04.498
You're always talking
about going to visit her.

06:04.532 --> 06:05.733
Liz is in Tahoe.

06:05.766 --> 06:07.568
Why can't I just
go to my mother?

06:07.601 --> 06:09.336
Okay. Okay.

06:09.369 --> 06:12.506
What are you gonna do?
What happens to you?

06:12.540 --> 06:14.675
Is my bag of stuff
still upstairs?

06:14.708 --> 06:15.776
Yeah.

06:15.809 --> 06:18.746
Okay.
Well, I'm gonna go get it.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.529
[ Beep ]

06:35.563 --> 06:38.065
Hey, Helen, It's Dr. Chance.
Listen.

06:38.098 --> 06:40.701
I've got a personal emergency,

06:40.734 --> 06:42.536
a family emergency,

06:42.570 --> 06:43.971
and I'm going to have
to close the office.

06:44.004 --> 06:47.875
So, uh, I'm sorry
about the short notice,

06:47.908 --> 06:49.076
but I'm going to call the agency

06:49.109 --> 06:51.378
and tell them
you did a great job.

06:51.411 --> 06:52.480
But there it is.

06:52.513 --> 06:54.448
Thanks for everything.
Bye.

07:01.489 --> 07:04.391
[ Ringing ]

07:04.424 --> 07:05.425
Jaclyn: Leave a message.

07:05.459 --> 07:06.627
[ Beep ]

07:06.660 --> 07:09.597
Hi, Jaclyn.
It's Eldon.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.899
Listen. Things --

07:11.932 --> 07:14.735
Things have, uh --
they've gotten really bad.

07:14.768 --> 07:18.572
I mean, really bad.
I need you to call me, please,

07:18.606 --> 07:20.974
as soon as you can.

07:33.186 --> 07:35.589
Chance: Darius sustained
a coma lasting 12 days,

07:35.623 --> 07:38.526
along with a compound fracture
of his right femur.

07:42.630 --> 07:43.831
Upon release
from the hospital,

07:43.864 --> 07:45.699
9-year-old Darius
was sent to live

07:45.733 --> 07:47.868
with his paternal grandmother,
Ruth Morrison.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.870
I don't want to keep him.
Well, who's gonna --

07:49.903 --> 07:51.539
The reason for this had to do

07:51.572 --> 07:53.674
with the devastating effect
the loss of his wife

07:53.707 --> 07:55.976
and elder son had
on Sanford Pringle,

07:56.009 --> 07:58.879
Darius's father,
who felt himself unable,

07:58.912 --> 08:01.849
or unwilling,
to see his surviving son.

08:04.051 --> 08:05.653
Ruth Morrison at that time

08:05.686 --> 08:07.487
was married to one
James Morrison,

08:07.521 --> 08:10.724
her third husband.

08:10.758 --> 08:12.125
Ruth stated that from the time

08:12.159 --> 08:14.962
of Darius's release
from the hospital,

08:14.995 --> 08:20.901
it was as if they had
to "raise him from infancy."

08:20.934 --> 08:24.738
Darius was unable
to feed himself.

08:24.772 --> 08:26.206
Poor balance
made it necessary

08:26.239 --> 08:29.209
for him to wear
protective headgear.

08:29.242 --> 08:32.145
After several months,
he began very slowly to recover

08:32.179 --> 08:35.683
a good deal of his memory
and language function.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.685
It was around this time
that James Morrison

08:37.718 --> 08:39.720
brought his son
from a former marriage

08:39.753 --> 08:43.591
to live with the family
in Oakland.

08:43.624 --> 08:44.925
Darius has stated that

08:44.958 --> 08:48.028
his grandmother knew
of the sexual abuse,

08:48.061 --> 08:49.763
but told him never
to speak of it,

08:49.797 --> 08:51.932
and would punish him
for doing so.

08:55.235 --> 08:58.772
This continued for a period
of roughly five years.

08:58.806 --> 09:00.007
[ Lock clicks ]

09:00.040 --> 09:02.576
At which point
Sanford Pringle returned

09:02.610 --> 09:05.012
in the company
of his new wife, Norma,

09:05.045 --> 09:06.947
20 years his junior.

09:11.084 --> 09:13.621
Darius reports that
his father was kind to him

09:13.654 --> 09:17.925
during the rare times
they were together,

09:17.958 --> 09:21.028
but was preoccupied with both
his skyrocketing career

09:21.061 --> 09:23.697
and his new family.

09:23.731 --> 09:25.799
On the single occasion
when Darius tried

09:25.833 --> 09:28.702
to talk to his father
about what had happened,

09:28.736 --> 09:31.872
it was "as if his father
was looking through him

09:31.905 --> 09:35.175
and could not hear
what was being said."

09:40.247 --> 09:43.050
Afterward, his father
continued to leave Darius

09:43.083 --> 09:46.553
at the home of his grandmother
whenever he was out of town

09:46.586 --> 09:47.788
to allow his new wife

09:47.821 --> 09:50.123
to concentrate
on their toddler son.

09:57.597 --> 09:58.999
By the age of 15,

09:59.032 --> 10:00.768
Darius had become preoccupied

10:00.801 --> 10:03.804
with books on warfare,

10:03.837 --> 10:05.973
the study of martial arts,

10:06.006 --> 10:10.110
and in particular, a book called
"Unlocking Your Hidden Powers."

10:15.148 --> 10:17.250
He'd also begun
to exhibit periods

10:17.284 --> 10:19.119
of what appeared
to be mood disturbance

10:19.152 --> 10:21.689
with intermittent
psychotic behavior.

10:21.722 --> 10:23.791
I don't know what he's doing.
It's horrible.

10:23.824 --> 10:25.125
This behavior culminated

10:25.158 --> 10:27.127
with the beatings
of James Morrison

10:27.160 --> 10:28.996
and his son Paul.

10:29.029 --> 10:31.999
Darius was taken into custody
by the Oakland Police,

10:32.032 --> 10:33.633
and later transferred to

10:33.667 --> 10:35.268
the state mental hospital
in Napa,

10:35.302 --> 10:38.105
where he remained
for a period of three months.

10:38.138 --> 10:40.741
[ Siren wails ]

10:42.642 --> 10:45.846
Lynn: So, you're seeing him
now as a patient?

10:45.879 --> 10:47.815
Yes. I will be.

10:47.848 --> 10:49.983
And you've already been
to Napa State, you said.

10:50.017 --> 10:51.184
I have.

10:51.218 --> 10:54.021
He was inpatient
there twice.

10:54.054 --> 10:56.857
First time for three months
when he was 15.

10:56.890 --> 10:59.960
Second time was just
a couple of days.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.628
And the second time,

11:01.661 --> 11:03.964
he was transferred
directly from here.

11:03.997 --> 11:06.800
Yes. Not directly, but yes.
What do you mean?

11:06.834 --> 11:09.036
Well, we turned him
over to the police first.

11:09.069 --> 11:11.238
After they took custody,
they contacted the family.

11:11.271 --> 11:14.074
Police?
What -- I'm confused.

11:14.107 --> 11:17.244
I can see that.
And I'm sorry to hear it.

11:17.277 --> 11:21.081
That would suggest that Darius
didn't get the help he needs.

11:21.114 --> 11:22.816
After Napa State,
he was released

11:22.850 --> 11:24.051
to his father's custody.

11:24.084 --> 11:26.186
There had been
a follow-up,

11:26.219 --> 11:28.655
but before there could be,
he ran away.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.257
Lived on the streets,
first in Oakland.

11:30.290 --> 11:33.193
How old was he?
Mm. 16.

11:33.226 --> 11:35.763
Made some money with his muscle,
being a street enforcer.

11:35.796 --> 11:37.664
Someone always needs something
done on the streets,

11:37.697 --> 11:41.334
a debt collected
or an enemy taken care of.

11:41.368 --> 11:44.337
After a few years of that,
he moved to Palo Alto.

11:44.371 --> 11:46.673
Lots of returning
military personnel there,

11:46.706 --> 11:48.675
guys from Afghanistan
and Iraq.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.343
He made a lot of friends.

11:50.377 --> 11:53.847
A buddy of mine keeps
going back to Afghanistan.

11:53.881 --> 11:55.749
This is what he likes.

11:57.717 --> 12:00.854
Is that where you were?

12:00.888 --> 12:02.422
Some of those vets
were still active duty,

12:02.455 --> 12:04.091
some were homeless.

12:04.124 --> 12:07.961
A lot were connected to
the V.A. Hospital in Palo Alto.

12:07.995 --> 12:11.131
A number of those men
were addicted to street drugs

12:11.164 --> 12:12.966
that Darius
could get for them

12:13.000 --> 12:15.903
because of his connections
with the Oakland dealers.

12:15.936 --> 12:19.139
But then Darius started
using the same drugs himself,

12:19.172 --> 12:22.876
to the point that they, in his
words, "became a problem."

12:22.910 --> 12:26.113
That's when he showed up here
with his fake military I.D. card

12:26.146 --> 12:28.816
that one of the guys
had gotten him.

12:28.849 --> 12:30.217
Fake?

12:30.250 --> 12:32.119
An operator I worked
with in Kandahar...

12:32.152 --> 12:34.054
When I came back
from my last tour...

12:34.087 --> 12:35.455
I was in the Teams.

12:35.488 --> 12:38.391
We used to run these drills,
sneak and peek.

12:38.425 --> 12:40.160
You mean he had
a fake I.D.?

12:40.193 --> 12:42.395
Yes.
Very well-executed.

12:42.429 --> 12:43.997
Totally legitimate-looking.

12:44.031 --> 12:47.234
At first glance,
even at second glance, it was --

12:47.267 --> 12:51.238
You're saying he was
never in the military?

12:51.271 --> 12:53.040
I'm saying he was not.

12:55.843 --> 12:57.811
First thing that
happens in combat,

12:57.845 --> 13:00.113
shit starts to fly
and so does your plan.

13:00.147 --> 13:01.748
After that, you improvise.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.017
He was admitted
through emergency services.

13:04.051 --> 13:07.454
He was treated for
chronic substance abuse

13:07.487 --> 13:09.422
and psychotic ideation.

13:09.456 --> 13:11.291
He had managed to detox

13:11.324 --> 13:13.126
and was just starting
to work with me

13:13.160 --> 13:15.762
when the ruse
was discovered.

13:15.795 --> 13:18.131
Fake I.D.

13:18.165 --> 13:19.466
That's when the police
were called?

13:19.499 --> 13:21.168
Yeah.

13:21.201 --> 13:23.136
They took him
back to Napa.

13:23.170 --> 13:26.974
His family transferred him
to a private facility in Marin.

13:27.007 --> 13:29.209
I tried to reach out,
but they said

13:29.242 --> 13:31.478
that he'd run away again.

13:31.511 --> 13:34.948
That's the last
I heard of him until now.

13:34.982 --> 13:37.317
You're gonna help him,
you said?

13:37.350 --> 13:40.120
I -- Yes.

13:40.153 --> 13:41.955
I'm glad.

13:41.989 --> 13:45.492
I actually argued for him
to stay here, but was overruled.

13:45.525 --> 13:47.794
I always wondered
what happened to him.

13:47.827 --> 13:50.163
But now, here you are.

13:53.433 --> 13:55.869
The world is full
of magic things

13:55.903 --> 13:59.472
patiently waiting for
our senses to grow sharper.

13:59.506 --> 14:01.041
Is that Yeats?

14:01.074 --> 14:03.310
Darius turned me on
to that one.

14:03.343 --> 14:06.546
An unusual guy.

14:06.579 --> 14:09.182
One of my very own.

14:17.024 --> 14:19.392
**

14:19.426 --> 14:23.196
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

14:25.532 --> 14:29.169
Carl: So, has any of
the family even come by?

14:29.202 --> 14:32.339
I mean, it's like the Kennedys.

14:32.372 --> 14:35.075
They had that poor girl
lobotomized.

14:35.108 --> 14:36.843
That's not gonna happen.

14:36.876 --> 14:38.545
It's much more difficult
to pull off these days.

14:38.578 --> 14:40.513
You haven't
met the family.

14:40.547 --> 14:44.351
They'll try
to pull something.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.553
They'll have him put away,
and we'll never see him again.

14:46.586 --> 14:48.355
They can't.
He's an adult.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.190
What if they give him
some drugs?

14:50.223 --> 14:52.425
Hmm?
And get him to sign something?

14:52.459 --> 14:55.028
No. Then he'll argue
that he was drugged.

14:55.062 --> 14:57.030
It's almost impossible
in this day and age

14:57.064 --> 14:58.565
to gain that kind
of conservatorship

14:58.598 --> 15:01.134
over someone
against their will.

15:01.168 --> 15:02.535
Disinheriting
someone is one thing.

15:02.569 --> 15:04.037
Having them put
away is another.

15:04.071 --> 15:05.939
You don't know the father.

15:05.973 --> 15:07.874
Do you?
I don't need to.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.242
I've seen
what he hath wrought.

15:09.276 --> 15:10.443
Well, I don't
know the family,

15:10.477 --> 15:13.380
but I read
the medical history.

15:13.413 --> 15:15.148
Honestly, it seems
like D's father

15:15.182 --> 15:17.050
is keen to be rid of him.

15:17.084 --> 15:18.551
Why would he care
about putting him away?

15:18.585 --> 15:20.087
I don't know.

15:20.120 --> 15:22.289
But he's been looking
for him for years.

15:22.322 --> 15:25.458
So, whatever
the reason, he cares.

15:25.492 --> 15:28.395
He's a wealthy and powerful man
with friends in high places,

15:28.428 --> 15:31.064
and he hates that boy.

15:31.098 --> 15:33.066
He hates him for
what he did to him.

15:33.100 --> 15:34.934
Or hates himself
for having allowed it.

15:34.968 --> 15:37.570
Whatever, he's gonna
take it out on D, either way.

15:37.604 --> 15:41.108
"You're not a superman, D,"
I tell him.

15:43.176 --> 15:45.278
He thinks he is,
you know?

15:47.614 --> 15:51.418
What he's got to think,
I suppose.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.585
Given everything.

15:52.619 --> 15:54.454
Which you knew.

15:54.487 --> 15:56.189
All of it.

15:56.223 --> 15:57.457
You couldn't have
just taken me aside

15:57.490 --> 15:59.326
and given me a heads up?

15:59.359 --> 16:00.927
I'm hiring him,
for Christ's sake.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.996
And not just to redo
my furniture.

16:03.030 --> 16:04.097
You know what for.

16:04.131 --> 16:05.432
He eats too many doughnuts.

16:05.465 --> 16:07.267
He is not criminally insane.

16:07.300 --> 16:08.601
And he's not
a veteran, either.

16:08.635 --> 16:13.106
Well, not of any war
on foreign soil, no.

16:13.140 --> 16:14.674
You still could have
said something.

16:14.707 --> 16:17.210
Not my something to say.

16:17.244 --> 16:19.946
It's his.

16:19.979 --> 16:23.316
You know, Carl, I --
I need a favor.

16:25.218 --> 16:27.220
What is it?

16:27.254 --> 16:28.488
I don't know how much
he told you

16:28.521 --> 16:30.023
about what happened
the other night.

16:30.057 --> 16:32.025
Enough.

16:32.059 --> 16:34.527
Okay. Well, since then,
my apartment --

16:34.561 --> 16:37.164
I can't go home.
I'm scared for my family.

16:37.197 --> 16:39.199
I had to send them away.
I don't have cash.

16:39.232 --> 16:41.334
I'm afraid
to use my cards.

16:41.368 --> 16:44.003
I'd ask D what to do,
but I can't.

16:44.037 --> 16:47.407
So, this is the only place
I have left.

16:49.542 --> 16:51.678
Stay as long as you like.

17:06.693 --> 17:10.263
[ Cellphone ringing ]

17:18.638 --> 17:19.672
[ Thud ]

17:19.706 --> 17:21.508
Oh, fuck.

17:21.541 --> 17:24.211
[ Ringing continues ]

17:31.751 --> 17:34.254
[ Groans ]

17:39.459 --> 17:40.693
[ Clears throat ] Hello?

17:40.727 --> 17:43.363
Hey, Doc.
Detective Hynes.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.265
I wake you?

17:45.298 --> 17:48.268
Uh, no.
Uh, yeah.

17:48.301 --> 17:50.203
I went by
your office yesterday

17:50.237 --> 17:52.071
since that worked
better the first time,

17:52.105 --> 17:53.706
but it was closed.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.442
Cardiologist
down the hall said

17:55.475 --> 17:58.645
he heard you're having
a family emergency?

17:58.678 --> 18:00.280
Yeah. I am.

18:00.313 --> 18:02.582
Well, I don't want
to intrude on that,

18:02.615 --> 18:04.251
but I do have
a couple more questions

18:04.284 --> 18:06.719
about Dr. Cohen.

18:06.753 --> 18:09.389
Following up on some
of the things you said that,

18:09.422 --> 18:11.691
maybe, aren't making
the most sense.

18:13.826 --> 18:14.794
Hello?

18:14.827 --> 18:16.463
Yeah. I'm here.

18:16.496 --> 18:18.631
Look, I'm not trying
to be patronizing, Doc,

18:18.665 --> 18:20.733
and I probably
don't need to remind you,

18:20.767 --> 18:24.171
but I am trying
to solve a crime here,

18:24.204 --> 18:27.106
a horrible crime,
done on an innocent person.

18:30.510 --> 18:33.180
He's smart, then.

18:33.213 --> 18:34.681
A guy like that
can be a problem.

18:34.714 --> 18:36.483
Chance: A homicidal
homicide detective?

18:36.516 --> 18:37.817
Yeah, I would say.

18:37.850 --> 18:39.752
He knows how
to game the system.

18:39.786 --> 18:41.621
He is the system.

18:46.859 --> 18:49.529
I'll answer your questions.

18:49.562 --> 18:52.165
All your questions.

18:58.638 --> 19:01.140
So, you didn't know
these guys who were, maybe,

19:01.174 --> 19:02.509
speaking Romanian?

19:02.542 --> 19:03.810
No.

19:03.843 --> 19:05.512
But they were definitely
in your apartment?

19:05.545 --> 19:07.314
Yes.

19:07.347 --> 19:09.282
Let me just --
I just want to make sure

19:09.316 --> 19:11.551
I'm understanding
everything.

19:11.584 --> 19:15.288
So, Stanford referred
Jaclyn Blackstone to you,

19:15.322 --> 19:17.624
and she told you that she was
seeing a therapist who died.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.527
That was Dr. Cohen.
Yeah.

19:20.560 --> 19:24.231
Then you gave Mrs. Blackstone
a referral to your friend,

19:24.264 --> 19:26.399
who she's seen,
maybe, six times,

19:26.433 --> 19:29.469
and then, Detective Blackstone
beat her up to make her stop.

19:29.502 --> 19:31.671
Is that when you wanted
to see Dr. Cohen's records?

19:31.704 --> 19:35.475
Is that how you found out
what happened to her?

19:35.508 --> 19:38.545
Uh, yeah. Not all of it.

19:38.578 --> 19:40.413
Right. You found out
the rest from the file

19:40.447 --> 19:42.249
at the D.A.'s office,
'cause you were there

19:42.282 --> 19:44.417
going through the proper
channels for Mrs. Blackstone,

19:44.451 --> 19:47.554
who you put back
into therapy with your friend.

19:47.587 --> 19:50.490
Then when Detective Blackstone
found out about that,

19:50.523 --> 19:52.359
he went and slashed
your friend's tires,

19:52.392 --> 19:54.327
about the same time
that he stopped by

19:54.361 --> 19:55.828
and gave you a beatdown.

19:55.862 --> 19:58.265
How am I doing so far?

19:58.298 --> 20:00.367
Yeah. That's it.
Pretty much it.

20:00.400 --> 20:02.435
Are you with this
Mrs. Blackstone?

20:02.469 --> 20:05.672
I mean, are you
with her, with her?

20:05.705 --> 20:07.874
No.

20:07.907 --> 20:10.209
Well, what if I told you
I don't give a shit if you are,

20:10.243 --> 20:12.712
because I'm not
the doctor-patient police

20:12.745 --> 20:14.714
or the adultery police?

20:18.217 --> 20:19.352
We just --

20:19.386 --> 20:21.788
Right. Gotcha.

20:21.821 --> 20:23.756
Waitress: Here you go.

20:23.790 --> 20:25.792
Thank you.

20:28.395 --> 20:30.730
So, Detective Blackstone

20:30.763 --> 20:32.799
beat his wife
for going to therapy,

20:32.832 --> 20:34.701
he hit your daughter,

20:34.734 --> 20:36.803
he stalked and harassed
you and your friend,

20:36.836 --> 20:37.870
and he beat you up.

20:37.904 --> 20:39.606
Oh, and he might
a part-owner

20:39.639 --> 20:43.209
in a brothel,
according to his wife.

20:43.242 --> 20:45.612
And, oh, yeah,
that might be connected to

20:45.645 --> 20:47.380
why he got stabbed
the other night.

20:47.414 --> 20:50.450
I don't want to forget that.
Am I leaving anything out?

20:50.483 --> 20:51.718
No.

20:51.751 --> 20:54.587
Are you leaving
anything out?

20:54.621 --> 20:57.290
No.

20:57.324 --> 20:59.258
Have you told
anybody else about this?

21:04.864 --> 21:05.965
No.

21:09.536 --> 21:13.406
You know, I used to have
this partner, Augie Freck.

21:13.440 --> 21:16.343
9, 10 years ago, when Augie
was still in uniform,

21:16.376 --> 21:17.644
he got a call from Fremont

21:17.677 --> 21:19.779
to an armed situation
in Oakland.

21:19.812 --> 21:21.814
Suspect shot him.

21:21.848 --> 21:25.752
Oakland cop gave him first aid
until the EMTs could get there.

21:25.785 --> 21:29.422
Got a Medal of Merit
for saving Augie's life.

21:29.456 --> 21:31.524
Now, guess who
that Oakland cop was?

21:33.693 --> 21:35.528
I knew you know that police

21:35.562 --> 21:36.929
don't like to go after
other police.

21:36.963 --> 21:38.531
That's why they call
the Internal Affairs

21:38.565 --> 21:40.967
the Rat Squad.

21:48.675 --> 21:51.310
Good thing is,
the only thing I hate

21:51.344 --> 21:54.447
more than a cop
going after another cop

21:54.481 --> 21:56.849
is a bad cop.

22:00.319 --> 22:03.823
So, what -- Does that mean
you're gonna help me?

22:03.856 --> 22:06.526
Well, yeah. I mean,
maybe I'm gonna

22:06.559 --> 22:07.960
look into it
and see what I find out,

22:07.994 --> 22:09.962
but let me tell you,
it's not gonna be easy.

22:09.996 --> 22:12.799
I mean, this guy has
a good reputation.

22:12.832 --> 22:15.902
I mean, fuck!

22:15.935 --> 22:18.304
Yeah.

22:18.337 --> 22:23.643
I know that, you know, my --
my choices have not been --

22:23.676 --> 22:27.980
I -- I have been culpable,
and I'm sorry.

22:28.014 --> 22:29.582
Don't be sorry, okay?

22:29.616 --> 22:31.984
You're not
the piece of shit here.

22:32.018 --> 22:33.920
He is.

22:33.953 --> 22:36.389
But, this is --
this is gonna get rough.

22:36.423 --> 22:37.824
I mean, enough to where,

22:37.857 --> 22:41.360
maybe I'm crazy for saying
I'll look into it.

22:41.394 --> 22:44.431
I mean, [chuckles] you're
the neuropsychiatrist.

22:44.464 --> 22:45.898
Am I crazy?

22:45.932 --> 22:48.901
[ Chuckles ] No.

22:48.935 --> 22:50.537
Okay.

22:50.570 --> 22:52.605
Are you?

23:01.648 --> 23:03.082
Man: Sir, there's
no visitors right now.

23:03.115 --> 23:05.518
Sanford: I know.
End of the hall, right?

23:05.552 --> 23:06.853
-Sir.
-Thank you. Appreciate it.

23:06.886 --> 23:08.387
Thank you.

23:38.651 --> 23:40.620
My God.
It really is him.

23:43.923 --> 23:47.460
Didn't think
I'd even recognize him.

23:47.494 --> 23:49.762
What can you tell us?

23:49.796 --> 23:52.398
Has there been any changes?

23:52.431 --> 23:54.400
You're...

23:54.433 --> 23:57.470
Eldon Chance,
neuropsychiatry.

23:57.504 --> 23:59.071
Oh, all right.

23:59.105 --> 24:04.577
So, we're looking at trauma
to the brain, structural damage.

24:04.611 --> 24:07.814
There's no evidence of that
according to the MRI.

24:07.847 --> 24:11.518
We're still waiting on an EEG
for signs of swelling.

24:11.551 --> 24:13.786
But the good news is that
he didn't have a seizure,

24:13.820 --> 24:16.689
there's no cardiac arrest,
no cerebral anoxia.

24:16.723 --> 24:20.426
Was his brain ever
without any oxygen?

24:20.459 --> 24:21.828
No.

24:21.861 --> 24:25.431
We expect him
to make a full recovery.

24:25.464 --> 24:28.701
I would hope that your son
would be more consistent

24:28.735 --> 24:30.837
in his monitoring
of his blood sugar levels.

24:30.870 --> 24:33.640
This was all very
foolish and avoidable.

24:37.544 --> 24:43.449
Would you be willing
to say that again under oath?

24:43.482 --> 24:44.951
I'm sorry?
What you just said --

24:44.984 --> 24:49.455
would you be willing to say
that again on the stand?

24:49.488 --> 24:50.823
I -- I don't
quite follow you.

24:50.857 --> 24:52.725
It's just that, for years,
I've been saying

24:52.759 --> 24:54.861
the exact
same thing you just said.

24:54.894 --> 24:57.664
My son cannot
take care of himself.

24:59.766 --> 25:02.802
Can he be transported
in his current state?

25:02.835 --> 25:06.573
I would say
that is not advisable.

25:06.606 --> 25:07.874
Good.

25:07.907 --> 25:09.976
So, let's say that
we were to set things up

25:10.009 --> 25:12.144
where we were to
care for him at home.

25:12.178 --> 25:15.715
Are you able
to make that call, Dr...

25:15.748 --> 25:18.818
I'm sorry.
Chance.

25:18.851 --> 25:20.219
No, I can't.

25:20.252 --> 25:22.555
That's something
for his team to discuss.

25:22.589 --> 25:24.657
When can that happen?

25:24.691 --> 25:27.927
I can't say.
Sorry. Soon.

25:27.960 --> 25:30.830
Look, I'm not trying
to be difficult here, Doctor,

25:30.863 --> 25:33.065
or overly dramatic,
and I don't know

25:33.099 --> 25:34.901
if you know
about my son's history.

25:34.934 --> 25:38.037
But I do want to be clear.
My son is dangerous.

25:38.070 --> 25:41.507
Yes, to himself,
as you've said, but also,

25:41.540 --> 25:44.010
and even more
to the point, to others.

25:44.043 --> 25:47.046
So, maybe knowing that,
you can understand my urgency,

25:47.079 --> 25:48.514
by wanting him to receive

25:48.547 --> 25:51.684
the appropriate care
and treatment.

25:51.718 --> 25:54.020
I can understand,
but I can't speak for the team.

25:54.053 --> 25:57.657
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have other patients to see.

26:02.829 --> 26:05.097
Woman: Chief ortho resident
to pre-op.

26:05.131 --> 26:07.299
Chief ortho resident
to pre-op.

26:30.289 --> 26:32.759
We need to talk,
motherfucker!

26:38.597 --> 26:41.200
You make me chase you,
you're just making things worse!

26:55.648 --> 26:56.949
Aah!

27:00.687 --> 27:02.254
Christ!

27:02.288 --> 27:03.856
God damn it!

27:03.890 --> 27:05.224
Fuck!

27:07.960 --> 27:11.798
[ Indistinct talking ]

27:11.831 --> 27:13.833
[ Cellphone rings ]

27:13.866 --> 27:15.702
Woman:
Sir, no cellphones.

27:15.735 --> 27:17.303
I need to take this.

27:19.171 --> 27:22.641
[ Ringing continues ]

27:24.811 --> 27:27.179
Jaclyn?

27:40.092 --> 27:42.228
I'm sorry
about this place.

27:42.261 --> 27:44.797
I had to think of somewhere
that no one would see us.

27:44.831 --> 27:46.298
It's okay.

27:46.332 --> 27:47.834
[ Sighs ]

27:47.867 --> 27:49.736
I don't even know
where to start.

27:52.705 --> 27:54.807
He sent men
to my apartment.

27:54.841 --> 27:57.877
They were waiting for me
when I got home.

27:57.910 --> 27:59.912
Did you --
I didn't go in, obviously,

27:59.946 --> 28:01.914
or I wouldn't be here.

28:01.948 --> 28:04.150
He probably had someone
watching while we were --

28:04.183 --> 28:07.219
No. He -- He hasn't
said anything.

28:07.253 --> 28:10.189
You said he likes
keeping people in suspense.

28:10.222 --> 28:11.891
Or maybe he thought
about it and decided

28:11.924 --> 28:13.993
he went too easy on you
the first time.

28:14.026 --> 28:15.227
Um, yeah.

28:15.261 --> 28:16.395
Or maybe he just
wants to make sure

28:16.428 --> 28:19.065
I have nothing
to come back to.

28:19.098 --> 28:21.934
What do you mean
"come back to"?

28:21.968 --> 28:24.203
We're leaving...

28:24.236 --> 28:29.175
tomorrow,
the next day, soon.

28:29.208 --> 28:32.678
Well, what about
the pension vesting?

28:32.711 --> 28:34.847
Eight months.
That was before.

28:34.881 --> 28:37.683
Now he thinks
they're after him.

28:37.716 --> 28:39.685
Who's "they"?

28:39.718 --> 28:41.187
Oh, his partners,

28:41.220 --> 28:43.856
whoever he competes with
in this sex business of his

28:43.890 --> 28:45.892
that I'm not supposed
to know anything about,

28:45.925 --> 28:48.861
whoever tried to kill him.

28:48.895 --> 28:51.197
He forgets that
sometimes people are around

28:51.230 --> 28:55.434
when he's talking
on the phone.

28:55.467 --> 28:57.203
Do you even know
where you're going?

28:57.236 --> 28:58.704
He would never tell me.

28:58.737 --> 29:00.406
You've got to stall.
You have to stall.

29:00.439 --> 29:02.208
I can't.
How would I?

29:02.241 --> 29:04.310
You've just got to push back.
You have to buy some time.

29:04.343 --> 29:06.879
We could make this work.

29:06.913 --> 29:09.248
I -- I just need
time to think.

29:09.281 --> 29:10.817
There's no time left.

29:10.850 --> 29:12.251
What about your daughter?
You can't leave her.

29:12.284 --> 29:13.953
He knows that.
It's better this way.

29:13.986 --> 29:16.122
For her.

29:16.155 --> 29:19.225
If he goes and I go with him,
then he's gone...

29:19.258 --> 29:22.394
out of her life.
Out of yours, too.

29:22.428 --> 29:24.730
It was such a beautiful
couple of days

29:24.763 --> 29:27.800
imagining what could be.

29:27.834 --> 29:29.135
You're such a good man.

29:29.168 --> 29:30.837
No. No. I --
No. It's true.

29:30.870 --> 29:34.740
Take it from someone
who knows the difference.

29:34.773 --> 29:38.244
You must want things,
but you just want them.

29:38.277 --> 29:40.412
You don't take them.

29:40.446 --> 29:41.814
You let me breathe.

29:41.848 --> 29:43.015
Jaclyn, please.

29:43.049 --> 29:44.984
No, I have to go.

29:45.017 --> 29:46.919
He's getting out
of the hospital today.

29:46.953 --> 29:49.021
I have to go pick him up.

30:11.310 --> 30:13.913
[ Sighs ]

30:22.021 --> 30:24.256
[ Cellphone chimes ]

30:28.494 --> 30:31.163
[ Sighs ]

30:56.923 --> 30:58.524
D: I don't know, brother.

30:58.557 --> 31:00.859
It's all just
police reports.

31:38.497 --> 31:40.266
Chance:
"The officer first on the scene

31:40.299 --> 31:42.901
reported that
at approximately 11:30 P.M.,

31:42.935 --> 31:45.904
Michael D. Ashville and his
brother, Dwayne Develle,

31:45.938 --> 31:48.040
were standing in front
of their apartment complex

31:48.074 --> 31:49.976
on Bancroft Avenue
in East Oakland

31:50.009 --> 31:52.178
when they were shot.

31:54.180 --> 31:57.283
When Detective Liem
and I interviewed Ms. Aubrey,

31:57.316 --> 32:00.552
she informed us she hikes daily
at Huckleberry Regional Preserve

32:00.586 --> 32:02.888
and usually arrives around
2:00 P.M.

32:02.921 --> 32:04.390
She was on her usual trail

32:04.423 --> 32:05.891
about a mile
from the parking lot

32:05.924 --> 32:08.060
when she discovered
Mr. Schorr.

32:08.094 --> 32:11.897
He appeared to have been stabbed
and was not breathing.

32:11.930 --> 32:14.000
First theory --
The killers went to the home

32:14.033 --> 32:15.234
sometime after midnight

32:15.267 --> 32:17.603
to either deliver
or collect various types

32:17.636 --> 32:20.072
and amounts of narcotics,

32:20.106 --> 32:22.574
that an argument ensued
either over the money

32:22.608 --> 32:25.577
or the possibility of bad drugs,
and the suspect, or suspects,

32:25.611 --> 32:30.316
armed with a knife
and gun, proceeded..."

32:30.349 --> 32:35.321
Courtney, Glaser, Jones.

32:35.354 --> 32:38.090
Mexico.

32:38.124 --> 32:40.926
D: That piece was old
that you were looking at.

32:40.959 --> 32:43.195
Black like that is onyx.

32:43.229 --> 32:45.464
Good ones are
hand-cut in Mexico.

32:45.497 --> 32:48.134
That was a good one.

32:50.969 --> 32:54.106
Chance: "November 10, 2012,

32:54.140 --> 32:55.641
the victim, Gayland Parks,

32:55.674 --> 32:58.610
was found bludgeoned
to death at his residence

32:58.644 --> 33:01.980
in an Oakland high-rise building
overlooking the harbor."

33:07.253 --> 33:10.989
Blackstone: Parks was naked,
handcuffed to his bed,

33:11.023 --> 33:14.493
with puncture wounds
in his arms.

33:14.526 --> 33:20.232
I, along with Homicide Team Two,
responded to investigate.

33:20.266 --> 33:24.036
There was no sign of
forced entry or struggle.

33:24.070 --> 33:26.305
The syringe on
the bedside table

33:26.338 --> 33:28.507
was later found
to contain heroine.

33:28.540 --> 33:31.410
Parks had extreme
blunt force trauma to the head.

33:33.512 --> 33:37.015
The weapon used was
a glass dildo found nearby.

33:43.589 --> 33:46.525
It was discovered the dead man
had a cellphone,

33:46.558 --> 33:50.429
believed to be missing
or taken during his murder.

33:50.462 --> 33:52.664
I obtained a warrant
for Parks' cellphone records

33:52.698 --> 33:55.534
and discovered the phone
was still being used.

33:55.567 --> 33:57.503
Got it right here.

33:57.536 --> 33:59.238
On the day following
the murder,

33:59.271 --> 34:01.673
several calls were placed
on Parks' phone

34:01.707 --> 34:03.609
to a Montclair cellphone number.

34:03.642 --> 34:06.712
The number was registered
to a woman named Lori Hammond,

34:06.745 --> 34:09.014
a 35-year-old single mother,

34:09.047 --> 34:12.618
currently employed
as a travel agent.

34:12.651 --> 34:14.353
When I interviewed
Lori Hammond,

34:14.386 --> 34:16.021
she told me
the Montclair cell number

34:16.054 --> 34:19.358
was part of her cellphone's
friends and family plan.

34:19.391 --> 34:21.760
She'd gotten it for her brother
Woody, a Gulf War veteran,

34:21.793 --> 34:24.463
who had been living
with her and her son.

34:28.267 --> 34:30.769
She stated that Woody
incurred serious body burns

34:30.802 --> 34:34.106
during his service,
that he has battled PTSD,

34:34.140 --> 34:35.707
along with substance abuse,

34:35.741 --> 34:37.543
but is now clean and sober,

34:37.576 --> 34:39.711
and has gone back
to school in San Diego

34:39.745 --> 34:41.747
to become a drug counselor.

34:41.780 --> 34:43.449
I contacted Mr. Hammond,

34:43.482 --> 34:46.218
who drove up voluntarily
to Oakland Police Headquarters

34:46.252 --> 34:49.221
to speak with me personally.

34:49.255 --> 34:52.057
He told me he had no problem
taking a polygraph exam

34:52.090 --> 34:54.426
and that I could search
his vehicle if I wanted.

34:54.460 --> 34:57.496
-In Mexico and Tijuana.
-So what, man?

34:57.529 --> 35:00.065
Prostitution's
legal down there, right?

35:00.098 --> 35:03.235
-Yeah. Yeah.
-How often you go?

35:03.269 --> 35:06.405
Um, once a week.
